
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-dane-srv-14.txt'>
    <title>"Using DNS-Based Authentication of Named Entities (DANE) TLSA Records with SRV Records", Tony Finch, Matthew Miller, Peter Saint-Andre</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-dane-srv-14.txt</link>
    <description>The DANE specification (RFC 6698) describes how to use TLSA resource records secured by DNSSEC (RFC 4033) to associate a server's connection endpoint with its TLS certificate (thus enabling administrators of domain names to specify the keys used in that domain's TLS servers).  However, application protocols that use SRV records (RFC 2782) to indirectly name the target server connection endpoints for a service domain cannot apply the rules from RFC 6698. Therefore this document provides guidelines that enable such protocols to locate and use TLSA records.</description>
    <dc:date>2015-04-23T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
